wikipedia_page.main: Elspeth Anderson Whyte (born 24 December 1926), later known as Elspeth Stephanson, is a British athlete. Whyte was born in Hendon, Middlesex in December 1926. She competed in the women's shot put and the women's discus throw at the 1948 Summer Olympics. In 1963, she was living in Queensland, Australia.
